Topic: Actions row construction & dropdown menu wiring
Rationale: makeBrowseRow currently builds the actions cell by appending Download/Delete/Move/Copy buttons directly. This is where the inline buttons must be replaced with a three-vertical-dots trigger that opens a dropdown menu containing those same actions, and where a 'contextmenu' (right-click) handler must be attached to the row to surface the identical menu. makeActionButton and the per-action handlers (delete/move/copy with confirm/prompt + rerender) must be preserved and reused inside the menu.
